      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SEBASTIANS WAITING (5) overcame a second row draw when making a winning return by close to 8m at Bendigo last week. That was his first outing for more than four months and he has won when second-up before so could progress enough to take this next step. MALIBUU (4) hasn't raced since tackling a hot field of mares in the G1 Macarthur Mile here in May but has been readied with two nice trials. Her best would take her close in this. SAN JUAN MOUNTAIN (2) continues to race well, placing in his last five attempts here. A low draw could see him break through. MAXIMUS MERIDIUS (3) enjoys a class drop after tackling the G3 Yamamoto Mile last start and owns a decent record at this circuit and distance.",
